{
  "intro": {
    "title": "Prepositions: Dependent",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "What dependent prepositions are",
        "content": "A **dependent preposition** is a fixed preposition that belongs to a specific verb, noun, or adjective — you cannot change it without sounding wrong. There is no general rule: you must **learn each combination as a chunk**.\n\nThey are very common in exams (gap-fill and open cloze), emails, and formal writing. Often the noun follows the same preposition as the verb/adjective it comes from: *interested **in** → interest **in***; *complain **about** → complaint **about***.",
        "diagrams": [
          {
            "type": "examples",
            "items": [
              {
                "bad": "I'm interested on history.",
                "good": "I'm interested in history."
              },
              {
                "bad": "It depends from the weather.",
                "good": "It depends on the weather."
              },
              {
                "bad": "a solution for the problem",
                "good": "a solution to the problem"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "root_ids": [
          "B2.collocations.dependent_prepositions"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "B2"
      },
      {
        "title": "The three families — verbs, nouns, adjectives",
        "content": "Group dependent prepositions by the word class they attach to — this is the most useful mental filing system.",
        "diagrams": [
          {
            "type": "table",
            "title": "Verbs + preposition",
            "headers": [
              "Verb",
              "Prep",
              "Example"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "depend",
                "**on**",
                "It depends on the weather."
              ],
              [
                "listen",
                "**to**",
                "Listen to the music."
              ],
              [
                "wait",
                "**for**",
                "Wait for me."
              ],
              [
                "apply",
                "**for**",
                "Apply for the job."
              ],
              [
                "complain",
                "**about**",
                "Complain about the noise."
              ],
              [
                "suffer",
                "**from**",
                "Suffer from headaches."
              ],
              [
                "consist",
                "**of**",
                "Consist of three parts."
              ],
              [
                "succeed",
                "**in**",
                "Succeed in the exam."
              ]
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "title": "Nouns + preposition",
            "headers": [
              "Noun",
              "Prep",
              "Example"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "reason",
                "**for**",
                "the reason for the delay"
              ],
              [
                "solution",
                "**to**",
                "a solution to the problem"
              ],
              [
                "answer",
                "**to**",
                "the answer to the question"
              ],
              [
                "increase",
                "**in**",
                "an increase in prices"
              ],
              [
                "interest",
                "**in**",
                "an interest in art"
              ],
              [
                "relationship",
                "**with**",
                "a relationship with colleagues"
              ]
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "table",
            "title": "Adjectives + preposition",
            "headers": [
              "Adjective",
              "Prep",
              "Example"
            ],
            "rows": [
              [
                "interested",
                "**in**",
                "interested in history"
              ],
              [
                "good",
                "**at**",
                "good at maths"
              ],
              [
                "afraid",
                "**of**",
                "afraid of spiders"
              ],
              [
                "proud",
                "**of**",
                "proud of her work"
              ],
              [
                "tired",
                "**of**",
                "tired of waiting"
              ],
              [
                "responsible",
                "**for**",
                "responsible for the project"
              ],
              [
                "worried",
                "**about**",
                "worried about the exam"
              ],
              [
