                "similar to mine"
              ]
            ]
          }
        ],
        "root_ids": [
          "B2.collocations.dependent_prepositions"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "B2"
      },
      {
        "title": "How to learn them + reference",
        "content": "Write the preposition together with the word (*depend **on***, not just *depend*). When you meet a new one, file it under Verb / Noun / Adjective. Full reference lists: **Reference → Dependent Prepositions**.",
        "diagrams": [
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "style": "cz",
            "text": "Czech prepositions rarely map onto English ones one-to-one. Dobře v matematice → good AT maths. Závisí na… → depends ON. Learn the English chunk, not the translation."
          }
        ],
        "root_ids": [
          "B2.collocations.dependent_prepositions"
        ],
        "cefr_level": "B2"
      }
    ]
  },
  "check": {
    "title": "Test your understanding",
    "root_ids": [
      "B2.collocations.dependent_prepositions"
    ],
    "cefr_level": "B2",
    "questions": [
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "Which sentence is correct?",
        "options": {
          "a": "I'm interested in history.",
          "b": "I'm interested on history.",
          "c": "I'm interested about history.",
          "d": "I'm interested for history."
        },
        "correct_option": "a",
        "explanation": "Dependent preposition (adjective): interested **in** something."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "Which preposition completes the phrase? 'It depends ____ the weather.'",
        "options": {
          "a": "of",
          "b": "from",
          "c": "on",
          "d": "about"
        },
        "correct_option": "c",
        "explanation": "Dependent preposition (verb): depend **on** something."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "Choose the correct noun + preposition pair.",
        "options": {
          "a": "a solution for the problem",
          "b": "a solution at the problem",
          "c": "a solution on the problem",
          "d": "a solution to the problem"
        },
        "correct_option": "d",
        "explanation": "Dependent preposition (noun): solution **to** a problem."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "Which preposition completes the phrase? 'She's afraid ____ spiders.'",
        "options": {
          "a": "for",
          "b": "from",
          "c": "of",
          "d": "at"
        },
        "correct_option": "c",
        "explanation": "Dependent preposition (adjective): afraid **of** something."
      },
      {
        "type": "mc",
        "question": "Which option completes the sentence? 'They complained ____ the noise.'",
        "options": {
          "a": "about",
          "b": "on",
          "c": "for",
          "d": "of"
        },
        "correct_option": "a",
        "explanation": "Dependent preposition (verb): complain **about** something."
      }
    ]
  },
